<section class="py-5 mt-5" style="background-color: #fef9e9;">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Page Title, Problem Description, and Symptoms -->
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-xl-6 text-center mx-auto">
        <!-- Title in one line -->
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2; color: #260d5e;">
          Immediate Actions After a Severe Allergic Reaction (Anaphylaxis)
        </h1>
        <!-- Brief problem description -->
        <p class="lead text-muted">
          Severe allergic reactions can escalate rapidly and require urgent intervention.
        </p>
        <!-- Short symptoms section in red -->
        <p class="fs-5" style="color: red;">
          <strong>Symptoms:</strong> Swelling, difficulty breathing, hives, and a rapid heartbeat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Main Content: Do's and What Not To Do -->
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Immediate Steps (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Call Emergency Services:</strong> Dial your local emergency number immediately.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Administer Epinephrine:</strong> Use an epinephrine auto-injector as directed if available.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Lay the Person Down:</strong> Help them lie down and, if possible, elevate their legs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Keep Them Calm:</strong> Reassure the person and monitor their condition closely.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Stay With Them:</strong> Remain by their side until professional help arrives.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not delay calling for help.</li>
          <li>Avoid administering additional medications without proper guidance.</li>
          <li>Do not allow the person to stand up or move excessively.</li>
          <li>Avoid panicking, as this may worsen the reaction.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-3">
          <em>Note:</em> This guide is for emergency use only and is not a substitute for professional medical treatment.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Column: Image Placeholder -->
      <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
        <!-- Replace the src with your actual image path -->
        <img src="/assets/img/allergy.png" alt="Allergic Reaction Steps" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
